text:
Looking for a Gulp/PostCSS solution for splitting CSS between difference files based on properties, anyone have any ideas for a plugin that might work here?

Use-case would be, for example, if there is a font style definition present in a module.css file that rule would be automatically removed and added instead to a global "fonts" stylesheet.

so in practice:

input module.css
```.example-class {
    margin-top: 1.2em;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: sans-serif;
    border: 2px solid;
}```
output module.css
```.example-class {
    margin-top: 1.2em;
    border: 2px solid;
}```
output fonts.css
```.example-class {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: sans-serif;
}```
